(
<figureCitation id="4EEDD7D9C75BFF91439AB8536591FBE5" box="[160,247,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1463,1487]" captionTargetBox="[171,1423,181,1429]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[163,1424,181,1439]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 8. Type specimens and label data. A: lectotype of Atheta (Dimetrota) altaica; B: syntype of A. (D.) sublaevana [= A. (D.) atramentaria]; C: holotype of A. (D.) sulputrida [= A. (D.) atramentaria]; D: lectotype of A. (D.) furtiva; E: holotype of A. (D.) machonryongica; F: holotype of A. (D.) photaechonica; G: lectotype of A. (D.) subsericans; H: syntype of A. (Dimetrota) weisei; I: holotype of A. (D.) chagangensis = A. (Badura) tokiokai." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571568" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571568/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">Fig. 8H</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9ECC98D7C75BFF9143ADB89B67C5FA7D" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D669CB5CC75BFF9143ADB89B6653FA95" blockId="10.[151,1437,1195,1509]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF9143ADB89B646DFB5D" bold="true" box="[151,267,1195,1221]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="11D6B0DFC75BFF914229B89B6751FB5C" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1907" box="[275,567,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="weisei" subGenus="Dimetrota">
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF914229B89B643AFB5D" box="[275,348,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">Atheta</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF914257B89B64B9FB5C" box="[365,479,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">Dimetrota</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF9142CBB89B6751FB5C" box="[497,567,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">weisei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded by 
<bibRefCitation id="B247B6ADC75BFF91403AB89B66FBFB5D" author="Pasnik, G." box="[768,925,1195,1221]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" pagination="185 - 234" refId="ref9470" refString="Pasnik, G. (2001) The North Korean Aleocharinae (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae): diversity and biogeography. Acta Zoological Cracoviensia, 44, 185 - 234." type="journal article" year="2001">Paśnik (2001)</bibRefCitation>
for the first time in 
<collectingCountry id="AEC18BCCC75BFF9147BEB89B6077FB5D" box="[1156,1297,1195,1221]" name="North Korea" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">North Korea</collectingCountry>
and by 
<bibRefCitation id="B247B6ADC75BFF914654B89B6447FB71" author="Cho, Y. B. &amp; Lafer, G. Sh. &amp; Paik, J. C. &amp; Park, J. K." pageId="10" pageNumber="411" pagination="35 - 44" refId="ref8865" refString="Cho, Y. B., Lafer, G. Sh., Paik, J. C. &amp; Park, J. K. (2002) Contribution to the Staphylinid Fauna (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae) of Korea. The Korean Journal of Soil Zoology, 7 (1 - 2), 35 - 44." type="journal article" year="2002">
Cho 
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF9143ADB8FF65AFFB71" box="[151,201,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">et al</emphasis>
. (2002)
</bibRefCitation>
for the first time in 
<collectingCountry id="AEC18BCCC75BFF91413EB8FF67F2FB71" box="[516,660,1231,1257]" name="South Korea" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">South Korea</collectingCountry>
. But, a habitus photograph of 
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF9140DDB8FF669EFB71" box="[999,1016,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">A</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="11D6B0DFC75BFF91473CB8FF61E7FB70" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1907" box="[1030,1153,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="weisei" subGenus="Dimetrota">
(
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF914735B8FF6145FB70" box="[1039,1059,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">D</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF914701B8FF61E7FB70" box="[1083,1153,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">weisei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
provided by the paper of Cho 
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF9143F7B8C36598FA95" box="[205,254,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">et al</emphasis>
. is incorrect identification of 
<taxonomicName id="11D6B0DFC75BFF914171B8C36653FA95" box="[587,821,1267,1293]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Gyrophaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF914171B8C367B0FA95" box="[587,726,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">Gyrophaena</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D669CB5CC75BFF9143FDB92767C5FA7D" blockId="10.[151,1437,1195,1509]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">
While studying Korean 
<taxonomicName id="11D6B0DFC75BFF9142F5B9276748FAA9" box="[463,558,1303,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Athetini">Athetini</taxonomicName>
, we found that this species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="11D6B0DFC75BFF9140DFB9276583FACD" authority="Gravenhorst (1802)" authorityName="Gravenhorst" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigritula" subGenus="Tetropla">
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF9140DFB9276148FAA9" box="[997,1070,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">Atheta</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF914707B92761FCFAA9" box="[1085,1178,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">Tetropla</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF914790B927606AFAA9" box="[1194,1292,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">nigritula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B247B6ADC75BFF914628B9276583FACD" author="Gravenhorst, J. L." pageId="10" pageNumber="411" refId="ref9019" refString="Gravenhorst, J. L. (1802) Coleoptera Microptera Brunsvicensia nec non exoticorum quotquot exstans in collectionibus entomologorum Brunsvicensium in genera familias et species distribuit. Carolus Reichard, Brunsuigae, 206 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 9568" type="book" year="1802">Gravenhorst (1802)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. After studying the 
<typeStatus id="096D75FEC75BFF9142F8B90B677FFACD" box="[450,537,1339,1365]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF914105B90B6736FACD" box="[575,592,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">A</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="11D6B0DFC75BFF914165B90B67BCFACC" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1907" box="[607,730,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="weisei" subGenus="Dimetrota">
(
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF914152B90B671AFACC" box="[616,636,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">D</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF9141AEB90B67BCFACC" box="[660,730,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">weisei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the 
<typeStatus id="096D75FEC75BFF914000B90B66C7FACD" box="[826,929,1339,1365]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF9140FDB90B66BEFACD" box="[967,984,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">A</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="11D6B0DFC75BFF9140DCB90B611FFACD" authorityName="Gravenhorst" authorityYear="1802" box="[998,1145,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigritula" subGenus="Tetropla">
(
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF9140D5B90B6699FACC" box="[1007,1023,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">T</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF91472DB90B611FFACD" box="[1047,1145,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">nigritula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we suspect that the character difference between these two species is insufficient to separate as different species. However, a more thorough comparative study including minute characters of specimens from broader distributional areas should be conducted to propose a synonym, 
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF9142A6B99764CBFA59" box="[412,429,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">A</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="11D6B0DFC75BFF914281B9976750FA58" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1907" box="[443,566,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="weisei" subGenus="Dimetrota">
(
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF9142FEB99764BEFA58" box="[452,472,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">D</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF9142CAB9976750FA58" box="[496,566,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">weisei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF9141BEB99767F3FA59" box="[644,661,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">A</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="11D6B0DFC75BFF914199B9976653FA59" authorityName="Gravenhorst" authorityYear="1802" box="[675,821,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigritula" subGenus="Tetropla">
(
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF914196B99767DAFA58" box="[684,700,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">T</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis id="E4A2174EC75BFF9141E9B9976653FA59" box="[723,821,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">nigritula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Almost Korean specimens were found on mushrooms and some were collected from FIT or bait trap.
</paragraph>
